This paper deals with image processing tasks such as image inpainting and image compressive sensing recovery, which are typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses sparse coding and rank minimization, which are topics commonly studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithm based on the alternating direction method of multipliers (ADMM), which is a popular optimization technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.MM, and cs.NA, in that order.
